524: ## Best Practices
525: 
526: ### 1. Start with Native Tools
527: 
528: Always check if Read/Write/Edit/Glob/Grep/Bash can solve the task before reaching for MCP tools.
529: 
530: ### 2. Use Serena for Symbol Navigation
531: 
532: When you need to find a specific function/class definition or its usages across the codebase.
533: 
534: ### 3. Incremental > Monolithic
535: 
536: Prefer Glob ‚Üí Grep ‚Üí Read over packing entire codebase with Repomix.
537: 
538: ### 4. Bash for System Commands
539: 
540: Git, gh, tree, ls, find, etc. are pre-approved and more flexible than MCP wrappers.
541: 
542: ### 5. MCP for Integration
543: 
544: Use MCP tools when you need external service integration (Linear, Context7) not available via native tools.
545: 
546: ### 6. Validate with Healthcheck
